    {
      "id": "graph-ref-focus-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Graph Reference Focus Propagation",
      "position": {
        "x": -480,
        "y": -220
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Graph Reference Focus Propagation\n\nA graph-reference node can host a focused fragment.\n\nWhen that fragment is focused, some inner node becomes locally selected or focused in practice. The host representation should be able to reflect that inner subject instead of staying visually mute.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
