    {
      "id": "graph-ref-focus-decision",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Current Rule",
      "position": {
        "x": 600,
        "y": -220
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Current Rule\n\nWhen a graph-reference fragment is focused, its current inner selection/focus should be eligible to project outward into the host representation.\n\nNot full detail necessarily, but enough to make the host representation semantically alive.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
