    {
      "id": "graph-ref-focus-task-graph-view",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Task Graph View Rule",
      "position": {
        "x": -1000,
        "y": 140
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Task Graph View Rule\n\nWhen the referenced graph is a **task graph**, its outward face should not stay generic.\n\nIt should surface:\n\n- the **goal** of the task graph\n- the **status** of that goal\n\nThat gives the host graph the two things a user actually needs immediately:\n\n- what this task graph is for\n- whether it is moving, blocked, or complete",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
